<div class="penelope">
  <img src="/img/welcomingcat.png" alt="Penelope the Neocities cat">
  <div class="penelope-Bubble">
    <p>Words are great, but you know what your page really needs? A picture of yours truly.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<p>Pictures use the <code><%= '<img>' %></code> tag, with two attributes:</p>

<ul class="lesson-List">
  <li><strong><code>src</code></strong> (source) &mdash; where the image file lives.</li>
  <li><strong><code>alt</code></strong> (alternative text) &mdash; a few words describing the picture, for people who can't see it. Screen readers speak it aloud, and browsers show it if the image fails to load.</li>
</ul>

<pre><code class="html"><%= '<img src="/neocities.png" alt="The Neocities cat">' %></code></pre>

<p>Surprise: <code><%= '<img>' %></code> has <strong>no closing tag</strong>. It doesn't wrap around any content &mdash; the image itself <em>is</em> the content &mdash; so the tag stands alone.</p>

<p>Good news: your Neocities site already comes with an image file called <code>neocities.png</code>, so you have something to show right away.</p>

<div class="your-Turn">
  <h4><i class="fa fa-pencil" aria-hidden="true"></i> Your turn</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Below your paragraphs, add: <code><%= '<img src="/neocities.png" alt="The Neocities cat">' %></code></li>
    <li>Write your own <code>alt</code> description if you like.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Check My Work</strong>.</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<div class="bonus-Box">
  <h4>Using your own pictures</h4>
  <p>After the tutorial, you can upload your own images on your <a href="/dashboard">dashboard</a>, then show them with <code><%= 'src="/yourpicture.jpg"' %></code>. The slash at the front means &ldquo;a file on my own site.&rdquo; You can also use a full address to show an image from another site.</p>
</div>

<script>
  function lessonCheck(doc, html) {
    var images = doc.querySelectorAll('body img')

    if(images.length == 0)
      return {ok: false, message: 'I don&rsquo;t see an ' + codeSample('<img>') + ' tag yet. Add ' + codeSample('<img src="/neocities.png" alt="The Neocities cat">') + ' below your paragraphs.'}

    var problem = null

    for(var i = 0; i < images.length; i++) {
      var img = images[i]
      var src = img.getAttribute('src')
      var alt = img.getAttribute('alt')

      if(src === null || src.trim() == '') {
        problem = problem || ('Your image tag needs a src attribute so it knows which picture to show: ' + codeSample('src="/neocities.png"'))
        continue
      }

      if(alt === null || alt.trim() == '') {
        problem = problem || ('Almost! Add a few words of alt text, like ' + codeSample('alt="The Neocities cat"') + ' &mdash; it&rsquo;s what people hear if they can&rsquo;t see the picture.')
        continue
      }

      return {ok: true, message: 'Picture perfect! And you added alt text like a pro.'}
    }

    return {ok: false, message: problem}
  }
</script>
